    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-10T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-10T23:00:00-05:00" n="822"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d822">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93/8–1149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            state</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-11T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 11, 1949—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:05 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 893. Military situation deteriorating so rapidly we may be compelled leave
                    Canton prior August 15.<note n="66" xml:id="d822fn66">In telCan No. 553, August
                        12, <ref target="#pg_1313">p. 1313</ref>, the Department authorized closing
                        the Embassy office “whenever in your judgment this move desirable”.</note>
                    Suggest therefore desirability expediting decision posed Cantel 883, August
                        5<note n="67" xml:id="d822fn67">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1308">p. 1308</ref>.</note> re
                    closing Canton Consulate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
